snippet: In addition to stolen items, the authorities said, a guard at a Victoria’s Secret in Herald Square discovered a dead fetus in the possession of two 17-year-olds.
abstract: New York Police Department says two teenage shoplifters stopped in Victoria's Secret store in Herald Square were also carrying dead fetus in one of their bags; young women are identified as Tiana Rodriguez of Brooklyn and Francis Estevez of Queens; two were charged with petty larceny, but medical examiner has scheduled autopsy of fetus that could lead to further charges.
lead_paragraph: In addition to stolen items, the authorities said, a guard at a Victoria’s Secret in Herald Square discovered a dead fetus in the possession of two 17-year-olds.

headline.main: Police Say Shoplifters Had Fetus in Bag
headline.print_headline: Police Say Shoplifters Had Fetus in Bag
